# Scytale · the Tleilaxu Face Dancer

Scytale is a Tleilaxu Face Dancer, a shapeshifter able to take the form and voice of others. In *Dune Messiah* he stands as a conspirator in the plot against Paul, and the instrument of that conspiracy is a gift: a ghola of the dead Duncan Idaho, cloned flesh offered as a poisoned lure. What he wears is never truly his own; what he gives is never truly free.

He is a creature of the Bene Tleilax, the masters of the axlotl tanks and of a forbidden biology that traffics in cloned flesh and stolen faces. Through Scytale, that secretive power reaches into the heart of the empire — sinister, inscrutable, and patient. He and his kind recur across the saga as a dark and unreadable force, never fully known and never to be trusted.

His nature is ethereal because he belongs to the unseen weave of the Dune universe — the realm of stolen identity and shifting form, where a face can be borrowed and a self concealed. The Face Dancer is a thing of surfaces that hide their depths, and Scytale moves through the story as an absence wearing the shape of a presence, a power felt more than seen.
